INTRODUCTION:



A Risk Management Plan has been implemented at the PMC Organometallix Carrollton production facility for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials.  This Risk Management Plan summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to the community of hazardous chemical releases.  The plan is organized to correspond with specific EPA RMP definitions and requirements, including:



?    PMC Organometallix policies;

?    Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;

?    Hazard Assessment;

?    Prevention Program;

?    Five year accident history;

?    Emergency Response Plan;

?    Planned changes to improve safety.



Risk management and safety have been important concerns at the Carrollton plant for many years; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities.  PMC Organometallix is committed to conducting its operations in a safe, responsible manner and to reducing risks to health and the environment.  



This commitment to health, environment, and safety (HES) starts with the Plant Manager.  Management routinely dedicates time for review of HES matters, including safety.  This emphasis on safety is carried through the facility, where plant personnel regularly review safety performance, take corrective actions, and strive for continuous improvement.  The success of PMC Organometallix HES programs is also reflected by a strong commitment to safety by employees and contractors.  



PMC ORGANOMETALLIX POLICIES:



PMC Organometallix HES programs include policies, procedures, standards, and guidance materials designed to fulfill the company's commitment to health, environment, and safety.  These materials include Risk Management Program guidance to help our facilities prevent and/or reduce the risk of accidents.  



FACILITY IDENTIFICATION AND REGULATED SUBSTANCES COVERED PROCESSES:



